The paper deals with complexity functions on words, which is a topic in discrete mathematics (cs.DM). It also involves the study of Sturmian words, which are related to number theory and combinatorics (cs.FL). The paper uses information theory concepts such as entropy and coding, which suggests a possible fit in cs.IT. The authors also use numerical methods to compute the cyclic complexity of words, which could place the paper in cs.NA. Finally, the paper discusses the Thue-Morse word, which is a well-known topic in computer science and automata theory (cs.SI).
